# Line-ending policy.
#
# Byte-exact golden reproduction is this repository's core invariant
# (tests/golden, calibration references), and several CI legs shell out to POSIX
# scripts (tools/*.sh). Git for Windows defaults core.autocrlf=true, so on the
# Windows CI runner text would otherwise be checked out CRLF and diverge from the
# LF-anchored goldens and scripts. Force LF in every working tree.
#
# macOS/Linux already check out LF (no CRLF is committed anywhere), so this is a
# no-op there: it introduces no renormalization diff and cannot change any
# existing file's bytes.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply text/EOL normalization. Explicit markers guard the
# 288 .npz device-grid goldens (and image assets) against git's text heuristic.
*.npz  binary
*.npy  binary
*.png  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.ico  binary
*.icns binary
